===Alternative spellings===
*[[gugyeol]]

===Etymology===
From Korean [[구결]] ([[口訣]], gugyeol), "phrase parting".

===Noun===
'''kwukyel'''

# One of three early systems for writing Korean phonetically with Chinese characters before the invention of the modern [[hangul]] ([[한글]]) script, resembling the old Japanese [[kanbun]] ([[漢文]]) style. The other two ancient Korean systems were [[hyangchal]] and [[itwu]].

====Characters====
'''Some of the ideograms that were used phonetically in kwukyel:'''
:[[丆]], [[乊]], [[厼]], [[壭]], [[罖]], [[卪]], [[朩]], [[亪]], [[仒]]

